Ibrahim Na’iddah, lawmaker representing Gusau II constituency at the Zamfara house of assembly, is dead. According to NAN, the development was confirmed in a statement by Mustafa Jafaru-Kaura, spokesman of the Zamfara assembly. Jafaru-Kaura said the lawmaker died on Saturday after a “protracted illness”. He is said to have died at the Federal Medical Centre (FMC) in Gusau, the Zamfara capital. He was buried on Saturday according to Islamic rites. “The remains of the lawmaker was finally laid to rest at the Gusau central cemetery along Gangaren Kwata area in Gusau, the state capital,” the statement reads “His funeral prayer was performed at the central Juma’at mosque at Kanwuri area in Gusau metropolis. “The funeral prayer was attended by the speaker, Zamfara state house of assembly, Nasiru Magarya; his deputy, Musa Bawa, and all members of the state house of assembly and other government functionaries in the state.” According to the statement, the Zamfara assembly also expressed condolence to the family of the deceased and prayed that “Allah grants him Aljannatul Firdaus”.